  "critical": false,
  "description": "Trans-1,4-polyisoprene from Palaquium tree latex. Hard, horn-like thermoplastic at room temperature, softens at 60-80°C. Harvested by felling trees and collecting coagulated latex. Processing: wash, masticate, roll into sheets. The ONLY practical underwater electrical insulation until polyethylene (1940s). Used for submarine telegraph cables, dental fillings, tool handles, electrical insulation.",
  "early_win": false,
